An authentification service.
Prerequisites:
You need to have node.js and mongodb installed on your computer and mongod instance running in shell on port 27017(default port). 
To start the server you have to execute "node index.js". Then you can access service from "index.html" or from terminal.
When working from terminal query to server should be in form of a POST query "login=your/login&psw=your/password&type_in='signin'|'login'"